{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "rsv:second-corinthians.2",
    "translationId": "rsv",
    "bookSlug": "second-corinthians",
    "chapterNumber": 2,
    "referenceLabel": "2 Corinthians 2",
    "summary": "Source text for 2 Corinthians 2 in Revised Standard Version."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "rsv:second-corinthians.2.1",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "second-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Corinthians 2:1",
      "text": "For I made up my mind not to make you another painful visit.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:second-corinthians.2.2",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "second-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Corinthians 2:2",
      "text": "For if I cause you pain, who is there to make me glad but the one whom I have pained?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:second-corinthians.2.3",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "second-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Corinthians 2:3",
      "text": "And I wrote as I did, so that when I came I might not suffer pain from those who should have made me rejoice, for I felt sure of all of you, that my joy would be the joy of you all.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:second-corinthians.2.4",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "second-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Corinthians 2:4",
      "text": "For I wrote you out of much affliction and anguish of heart and with many tears, not to cause you pain but to let you know the abundant love that I have for you.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:second-corinthians.2.5",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "second-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Corinthians 2:5",
      "text": "But if any one has caused pain, he has caused it not to me, but in some measure—not to put it too severely—to you all.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:second-corinthians.2.6",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "second-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Corinthians 2:6",
      "text": "For such a one this punishment by the majority is enough;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:second-corinthians.2.7",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "second-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Corinthians 2:7",
      "text": "so you should rather turn to forgive and comfort him, or he may be overwhelmed by excessive sorrow.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:second-corinthians.2.8",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "second-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Corinthians 2:8",
      "text": "So I beg you to reaffirm your love for him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:second-corinthians.2.9",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "second-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Corinthians 2:9",
      "text": "For this is why I wrote, that I might test you and know whether you are obedient in everything.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:second-corinthians.2.10",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "second-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Corinthians 2:10",
      "text": "Any one whom you forgive, I also forgive. What I have forgiven, if I have forgiven anything, has been for your sake in the presence of Christ,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:second-corinthians.2.11",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "second-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Corinthians 2:11",
      "text": "to keep Satan from gaining the advantage over us; for we are not ignorant of his designs.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:second-corinthians.2.12",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "second-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Corinthians 2:12",
      "text": "When I came to Troas to preach the gospel of Christ, a door was opened for me in the Lord;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:second-corinthians.2.13",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "second-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Corinthians 2:13",
      "text": "but my mind could not rest because I did not find my brother Titus there. So I took leave of them and went on to Macedonia.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:second-corinthians.2.14",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "second-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Corinthians 2:14",
      "text": "But thanks be to God, who in Christ always leads us in triumph, and through us spreads the fragrance of the knowledge of him everywhere.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:second-corinthians.2.15",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "second-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Corinthians 2:15",
      "text": "For we are the aroma of Christ to God among those who are being saved and among those who are perishing,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:second-corinthians.2.16",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "second-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Corinthians 2:16",
      "text": "to one a fragrance from death to death, to the other a fragrance from life to life. Who is sufficient for these things?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:second-corinthians.2.17",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "second-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Corinthians 2:17",
      "text": "For we are not, like so many, peddlers of God's word; but as men of sincerity, as commissioned by God, in the sight of God we speak in Christ.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
